The 7.8-magnitude tremor struck just after midnight on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - New Zealand emergency services and defence personnel have evacuated hundreds of tourists and residents from a small South Island town amid more strong aftershocks in the wake of a powerful earthquake that's killed two people.The 7.8-magnitude tremor struck just after midnight on Sunday, destroying farm homesteads, sending glass and masonry toppling from buildings in the capital, wellington, and cutting transport links across the northeast of the South Island.As aftershocks continue to rattle the region, emergency services have cordoned off streets in Wellington and evacuated several buildings, fearing that one might collapse.(Edited by Neo Koza)